pages.text:
Rider Support
Sag Stops are posted about every 15 miles.   Porta-potties are provided along the route. Volunteers can handle minor problems, but you should be prepared and have your bike in good working order before you arrive. We recommend you carry a cell phone, and at the rider start, a number will be provided for you to call if you encounter difficulty.
Refunds and Transfers
There are no refunds, however registrations can be transferred to another rider through 12/31/24.  A 15% transfer fee will be applied.
Registration
Registration opens on Friday, Oct. 1 via
bikereg.com
. An early bird rate of $75 will apply until Oct. 14. On Oct. 15, the regular rate of $100 will apply.
Volunteers
If you are interested in volunteering, please
contact us here
. A great event depends upon great volunteers.
Whether you are new to the area or if you are a seasoned veteran, all help is welcomed! Ride marshals will ride the entire event, but must be CSO Members familiar with trails. There is something of interest for everyone. Volunteering is a great way for non-riders or family members to participate in the fun.
Rules and Regulations
Helmets are required.
All riders must be registered. Portions of the event will take place in the south side of the park, where cyclists are normally prohibited. Unregistered riders found here will be considered trespassing.
Location
The Tour will start and finish at the San Felasco Hammock Preserve State Park’s north trailhead, located at 13201 San Felasco Parkway, Alachua, FL 32615.
Rider Check-In
Early check-in will be available starting at 6 p.m. on Friday, Jan. 10 at
Cypress & Grove Brewing Co.
, located at 1001 NW 4th St, Gainesville, FL 32601. Check-in will also be available Saturday morning at the trailhead pavilion beginning at 7:15.
